The paper deals with graph algorithms and complexity, which are central topics in computer science. The focus on sparse graphs suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) or cs.CG (computational geometry). The use of reductions and conditional lower bounds suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.DM (discrete mathematics) or cs.GT (computational complexity and cryptography). Finally, the specific problems studied in the paper (Shortest Cycle, APSP, Radius, etc.) suggest that the paper may also belong to cs.CC (computational complexity).
